    "The results of the sentiment scores of these texts are shown in Fig. 5.",
    "Meanwhile, we provide word clouds for both types of text data (showing the high frequency words), as shown in Fig. 6, where the language is Chinese, because our context is the Chinese stock market.",
    "As shown in Table 5, we mark the terms that occur most frequently.",
    "Figure 5 demonstrates that practitioner comment data has more sentiment variation and that the public influences individual sentiments.",
    "News media, however, have more severe sentiments (positive emotions tend to be 1 and negative emotions tend to be 0) and are predominantly positive, indicating that news is always presented with a bias."
